// WebSocket Handler Manager
// Holds a singleton reference to the WebSocket handler so MCP tools can broadcast without circular imports.

The handler is null until explicitly initialized via initializeWebSocketHandler.

FUNCTION initializeWebSocketHandler(handler) -> void                                    EXPORT
  Store the provided WebSocketHandler as the global singleton.

---

FUNCTION getWebSocketHandler() -> WebSocketHandler | null                               EXPORT
  Return the current global handler, or null if not yet initialized.

---

FUNCTION hasWebSocketHandler() -> boolean                                               EXPORT
  Return true if the handler has been initialized.
